The paper deals with the convergence analysis of the Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm for truncated mixtures of two Gaussians, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), dynamical systems (cs.DS), control theory (cs.SY), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of techniques from dynamical systems and stability analysis suggests that cs.DS and cs.SY are likely categories, while the focus on machine learning and statistical inference suggests cs.LG and cs.IT. Finally, the numerical aspects of the problem, such as the use of Monte Carlo simulations, suggest cs.NA as a possible category.
